Household income levels are also rising, and are expected to grow significantly, which will increase the demand for livestock products. The annual global per capita GDP is expected to increase from US$9,644 in 2010 to US$13,874. During the same period, the GDP per capita of South Asia is projected to increase from US$1,283 to US$3,890. It is projected that the demand for livestock products will double by 2050 owing to improvements in the standard of living (
 Garnett, 2009; 
 Rojas-Downing etÂ al., 2017).
